caption: My first visit for a candlelight piano concert this evening. Show started at 730, ends at 8:45, but they allowed us to enter at 7pm. Seating is open so arrive around 6:45 for the best seats (where you can view the piano keys as it's incredible to see how it's played). The church is smaller sized but still very beautiful. The size seems to complement these concerts as it's a more intimate crowd.  The woman performing was extremely talented and the ambiance was even somewhat romantic. Very lovely event overall (although the older man checking tickets could answer people when they greet him with a bonsoir...).
Lovely little church. They do intimate classical concerts inside as well.
Always a pleasure to participate to concerts organised in this beautiful Church.
Attended a Chopin piano concert in this cozy church. The acoustics and atmosphere were surreal. They have various musical events throughout the year on their website.

Tiny church in Latin quarter, occasionally hosts small concerts. We were fortunate to get tickets to an intimate candlelight piano recital of several pieces by French composers. The pianist was unbelievable. 70 minutes. Highly recommend!!
Been on the concert here. It was awesome. And the church itself is also beautiful and full of atmosphere. Feel free to visit it at any time, but highly recommend to go to listen the music.
Beautiful small church with extremely good concerts of classical music. Highly recommended to visit!
A simply beautiful small church where some exquisite music is played. A memorable evening in Paris.
Attended a Chopin piano concert in this cozy church. The acoustics and atmosphere were surreal. They have various musical events throughout the year on their website.
Look online for the small concerts that are available here. The intimate setting is wonderful and a great event to add to your trip!
Attended awesome piano concert there. Just wonderful. Sounds great! So many positive emotions...

Went there for a piano recital by candlelight. Wonderful cozy little space with old architecture adding an element of elegance. If you go in winter, bring a little extra layer so that you can take off your coat but still be comfortable.
Went to see Chopin by candlelight.  A delightful young pianist and a unique setting for such an experience.
It is very intimate with great acoustics. Seats are typically uncomfortable. Easy to walk right by the little courtyard without noticing.
Beautiful candlelight classical music performance
I shed tears with a touching performance. Thank you. Pascal Mantin, the piano player.
Here I saw a classical music concert ! So beautiful was the music in such a spiritual place !!!!
Worth a visit. We went for a piano recital and discovered this church.
First time experience. That was awesome great amazing. Looking forward to my next one already. Wow. Mind blown
wonderful church and candle light concert

Great place for a small piano recital. I saw a local pianist play Liszt, Debussy, Chopin, etc. The old church was dimly lit with candles. Great atmosphere. I don’t speak French at all but I play piano. With the music, there was no language barrier. Loved it!
Great place for concepts and classical music in Paris!
Beautiful place with great acoustics, perfect for a concert.
Caught a piano concert here, acoustics were amazing and the space is intimate.
Our concert was just wonderful- beautiful music, lovely atmosphere and fab location.
A breathtaking performance by two phenomenal musicians performing a mix of Mozart and Beethoven on violin and piano. If you have a spare evening in Paris, it’s well worth the effort.
Attended a candlelight piano concert - magical!
The church is beautiful and with an outstanding acoustic. I went to a piano recital and it was delightful.
Holds regular classical concerts from the National Conservatory of Music of Paris.
Nice hidden church to step back from the neighborhood and relax a bit
Was there for a lovely piano concert. Very nice small church with a lot of charm.
It’s a pretty church
It's unusual for a church to feel cozy, but this one is exactly that. Special place to hear a piano concert.
We were fortunate enough to listen to a great concert in this quaint little chapel where it is said that Saints Francis Xavier and Ignatius of Loyola have prayed.
Elio di Tanna gave us a magnificent candlelit performance of a number of pieces by Chopin. Unforgettable.
Nice candlelight piano concert. Arrive early for best seats.
There was this beautifully  organized trio concert  event... it was so refreshing. The church is small and old...history
Splendid piano play ever.
